radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal bibasilar atelectasis; a small 4 mm hypodensity in the dome of the liver likely represents a small cyst or biliary hamartoma; 6 mm hypodensities in the lower pole of the right kidney and mid pole of the left kidney likely represent cysts; the tip of the appendix is dilated up to 9 mm with significant surrounding stranding; severe widespread diverticulosis; no evidence of free air or free fluid.
